verbose_text: The results (XREF_FIG) showed that GNAI3 knockdown by shGNAI3-GFP inhibited SCAPs growth over 2-6 days after transduction (P < 0.01) in an apparent time dependent manner (XREF_FIG), as well as cell cycle progression, as evidenced by G1 phase arrest (increased G1-phase cells) and decreased S and G2-phase populations of GNAI3 deficient SCAPs (P < 0.05; XREF_FIG).
evidence: GNAI3 knockdown by shGNAI3-GFP inhibited SCAPs
